    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A white, crystalline substance, glyceryl stearate, (C18H35 O2)3C3H5, found in the solid portion of most animal and vegetable fats and used in soaps, adhesives, textile sizes, etc. It is a glyceril ester of stearic acid.</Note_Text>
